  "structural_observation": "At alpha = 0.95 with n_calib = 19, the finite-sample ceil((n+1)*alpha) = 19 = n rank pins q_hat to the maximum calibration nonconformity score regardless of weighting; locally-weighted CP cannot differ from global CP at this level. At alpha = 0.90 and 0.80 the rank is < n and local weighting can act.",
  "interpretation": "Sweeping \u03b2 from 0 (global quantile) upward localises the calibration weighting around each test molecule. Compare coverage at \u03b1 = 0.80, 0.90, 0.95 to disentangle the structural pinning at \u03b1 = 0.95 from a real local-weighting effect at lower \u03b1."
